node.text:
HighKey is growing so fast, and by far one of the questions I get asked the most is “how do you build a scaleable business?” 🔑

In order to do this, you must:

1. Have a winning product/service. This allows for sales/closes to come fairly easy 🔥

2. Build a team of elite leaders: have people on your team who are smarter than you and action takers 💎

3. Create processes for your team to follow. You start with 1-2 workers first, then those steps change over time. Remember, the steps that get you from 0-$1000 aren’t the same as the ones to get you from $1000-$10,000 💰 

Keep those things in mind and you can grow very quickly 👀

node.title: How to Build a Scaleable Business

node.text:
Your online presence is a top priority in the world of social media 🔥

Your entire online presence determines the overall view that people have of you. So, you need
to spend time where massive audiences are 💎

This goes for all levels of business, whether you’re investing in your personal brand or a
high-level business, social media is the key to growing your brand 🚀

Our business values this so much that we are constantly telling our employees to up their social
media brand. Creating that overall presence is necessary for people to take you seriously
nowadays 🔥

Let us take care of your online presence, you need to be HighKey in the social media society!

node.text:
Want to increase your value in the marketplace? 📈

We can’t stress enough how important it is to grow your brand in online marketing.

You always want to be investing in your own personal brand to make yourself more valuable and to place yourself in a favourable position in the marketplace.

It truly is an investment, the time and effort that you put into your brand is correlated to an increase of self-worth. 

Providing value to the marketplace, a client, a business, etc., is part of the fundamental building blocks for long-term relationships and success. 

Are you investing the right amount of time and effort into your personal brand? 

Comment below ⬇️

node.title: Increase Your Value In The Marketplace

WHERE DO YOU SEE YOURSELF IN 10 YEARS.⠀
⠀
It’s not important in the day to day, but it’s crucial for the macro of your life and the direction of where you want to go.⠀
⠀
For example, I want to be connecting the biggest people together on a specific event. Right now it’s a podcast for all of our clients at HighKey Agency, and I’m a booking agent.⠀
⠀
After filming this video, I connected our biggest client Stefan Aarnio with Logan Paul’s podcast, by leveraging my other big connections I had that could benefit them.⠀
.⠀
Where do you see yourself in 10 years? Comment below!

node.text:
Your connections have everything to do with how successful you’re going to be.⠀
⠀
You always want to be building connections with everyone in your space, consistently growing that rolodex of people.⠀ ⠀
Who you know right now isn’t going to take you to the place you want to be. The more people the better.⠀
⠀
But it’s all about the quality of the people you know. If you know a bunch of people that do nothing, then what’s the point?⠀
⠀
You should always be trading and exchanging value. If you can provide value to the person you’re connecting with, it’ll make that relationship that much stronger.⠀
⠀
Are you making connections? Comment below

node.text:
2 THINGS TO CONSIDER:⠀
⠀
1. Who are you networking with?⠀
2. What value can you offer them?⠀
⠀
You’re trying to build a relationship. You can’t be asking for something- you have to be offering something of VALUE.⠀
⠀
So what’s of value to them? It depends on what you’re hitting them up for. What’s your purpose? Why are you reaching out to them?⠀
⠀
For example, I book podcasts. For one of our clients Stefan Aarnio, we’ve had some big names on his podcast like Robert Kiyosaki and Ryan Serhant.⠀
⠀
How I get these people, is to offer them a chance to be on the podcast guest and they like that. ⠀
⠀
Everyone wants to be heard and interviewed, and it’s of value to them because it helps push their personal brand or business forwards.⠀
⠀
You’d be surprised who responds if you have something relevant to offer them for free. People with hundreds of thousands or millions of followers will answer.⠀
⠀
Keep trying. How do you connect with people? Comment below ⬇️

node.text:
@chriscavallini has been with us for over 2 years now‼️

Today marked the day where we met in person for the first time. Over the past couple of years we’ve worked with Chris on developing his personal brand.

We’ve used a combination of social media management, social growth and press to get to the point we’re at today. 

To give a little bit of background, before Chris’ 18th birthday he was arrested 17 times and later on served jail time for distribution of anabolic steroids. 

Nowadays Chris is managing a multi-million dollar high quality meal plan business called @nutritionsolutions 🥗

We’re extremely happy to call Chris a great friend of ours and we can’t wait to be managing @nutritionsolutions as well🔥

📸 @dreamanthony_ 

#highkey #highkeyenterprise #highkeyagency

node.text:
HighKey is growing so fast, and by far one of the questions I get asked the most is “how do you build a scaleable business?” 🔑

In order to do this, you must:

1. Have a winning product/service. This allows for sales/closes to come fairly easy 🔥

2. Build a team of elite leaders: have people on your team who are smarter than you and action takers 💎

3. Create processes for your team to follow. You start with 1-2 workers first, then those steps change over time. Remember, the steps that get you from 0-$1000 aren’t the same as the ones to get you from $1000-$10,000 💰 

Keep those things in mind and you can grow very quickly 👀

node.text:
Your online presence is a top priority in the world of social media 🔥

Your entire online presence determines the overall view that people have of you. So, you need
to spend time where massive audiences are 💎

This goes for all levels of business, whether you’re investing in your personal brand or a
high-level business, social media is the key to growing your brand 🚀

Our business values this so much that we are constantly telling our employees to up their social
media brand. Creating that overall presence is necessary for people to take you seriously
nowadays 🔥

Let us take care of your online presence, you need to be HighKey in the social media society!

node.text:
Investing in your brand is the SINGLE most important decision you can make! 🔥

The long-term benefits of branding include a credible and personable reputation online. It's hard to draw a direct R.O.I with branding because the value is paid back in so many ways that it just takes time. 🤝

Direct marketing on the other hand is a short-term investment that primarily focuses on getting a R.O.I quickly. 💰

For every $1,000 you spend on Direct Marketing, you should be spending 5X that on your brand! 💸💰

Want to start leveling up? DM us now! 📲 ⬅️

node.text:
Want to increase your value in the marketplace? 📈

We can’t stress enough how important it is to grow your brand in online marketing.

You always want to be investing in your own personal brand to make yourself more valuable and to place yourself in a favourable position in the marketplace.

It truly is an investment, the time and effort that you put into your brand is correlated to an increase of self-worth. 

Providing value to the marketplace, a client, a business, etc., is part of the fundamental building blocks for long-term relationships and success. 

Are you investing the right amount of time and effort into your personal brand? 

Comment below ⬇️

node.text:
Growing your personal brand is the 🔑 to success no matter what you are doing.

A digital personal brand is how you can create a relationship with people that have never met you, by connecting with different aspects of how you portray yourself through your brand.
 
Here are 4 ways to grow your personal brand:

1.  Start creating content. Doesn't matter what type of content (video, picture or written copy), just start doing it! 

2. Try and collaborate with people in your industry. 

3. Spend time on all social media platforms, but mainly focus and master one social media perform at a time. 

4. Figure out ways to give the most value possible to your audience. Think about the "NEEDS" of your audience.
